  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">From Law to Practice - Making the Equality Act Work</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to support community groups across Wales, Scotland and England to utilise the Equality Act of 2010 in holding public sector bodies to account. The act places duties on public bodies to recognise citizens&apos; rights under eight strands of equality. The project is intended to inform community groups about the Act and to support and empower them to develop advocacy strategies to claim rights enshrined in the Act.</narrative>
  </description>
